<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1802,2045]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1802,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce, 2019" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[282,352,1804,1829]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[282,352,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[360,441,1803,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[360,441,1803,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possesses lateral pronotal carinae terminating on the ventral margin of the prothorax, a character shared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[394,483,1839,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myndus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[394,483,1839,1865]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myndus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but lacks the denticle of the forecoxae (
<figureCitation box="[921,988,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,997,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,995,1955]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Front leg of adult male Myxia gen. n. belinda sp. n. demonstrating lack of denticle on forecoxa (FC), location where denticle is present in Myndus in white circle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557841/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), a feature shared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[1244,1359,1839,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1244,1359,1839,1865]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Tegulae evident and tibiae of hind legs lack spines (tribal feature of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muir" authorityYear="1922" box="[847,947,1875,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Oecleini">Oecleini</taxonomicName>
). The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce, 2019" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[1085,1155,1876,1901]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1085,1155,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1161,1239,1875,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1161,1239,1875,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be diagnosed from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[214,329,1911,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,329,1911,1937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[387,476,1911,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myndus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[387,476,1911,1937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myndus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the overall form of the gonostyli. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce, 2019" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[940,1010,1912,1937]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[940,1010,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1019,1099,1911,1937]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1019,1099,1911,1937]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the gonostyli appear distally bifid, possessing a dorsal process near the terminus of each gonostylus in lateral view pointing dorsad and in ventral view, and a lateral tooth on the inner margin with an acute apex. In addition, medioventral process of pygofer is subtriangular. Phallobase separated from aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
